By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post)  –  The Ebonyi People Democratic Party National Assembly caucus has distanced itself from the defection of the state governor, Dave Umeahi to the All Progressives Congress. Senator Sam Egwu who led the other lawmakers from Ebonyi at the press briefing journalists at the National Assembly, accused Umeahi of being ungrateful to a party that have offered him everything- including 8 years as governor of Ebonyi state. Recall that Governor Umeahi yesterday dumped the PDP and defected to the All Progressives Congress. According to Senator Egwu: the reason given by Governor Dave Umeahi for Defection is now in the public domain. “This is a man who was a state official member at different times before becoming governor for eight years in the party. If there is anybody who should be grateful to the party it should be Umeahi. Details soon….. By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Nationsl Working Committee of the Peoples Democratic Party rose from a crucial meeting November 17, 2020 and announced the dissolution of the ward, local government and state executive committees of the Ebonyi state chapter of the party forthwith. The NWC has also… November 18, 2020 In "Top Stories" THERE was disquiet in the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) on Tuesday, following the defection of Ebonyi State Governor David Umahi to the All Progressives Congress (APC). It was learnt that the defection unsettled the party’s leadership after making a last-minute effort to dissuade Umahi from leaving its fold. The party… November 18, 2020 In "Politics" By Chibuike Nwabuko  Abuja （Sundiata Post）- South-East Governors Forum on Friday proscribed the activities of Indigenous People Of Biafra, IPOB in the five states of the South East. The announcement was made after the meeting of the governors that took place at Enugu Government House on Friday. Chairman of the… September 15, 2017 In "Top Stories"